                        <head>31. Editorial Note</head>
                        <p>On December 18, President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> sent Vice President <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> as his personal representative to
                            Austria for first-hand information about the Hungarian refugee
                            situation. Regarding the Vice President’s visit, see <ref target="frus1955-57v25#pg_534">volume XXV, pages 534</ref>–<ref target="frus1955-57v25#pg_539">539</ref>.</p>
                    </div>
